%I A397707 #6 Jul 11 2026 20:59:00
%S A397707 4,22,164,1414,13260,131182,1347280,14225772,153450876,1683580892,
%T A397707 18728356336
%N A397707 Number of face-connected components of n polyhedral cells in the bisymmetric hendecahedral honeycomb, up to translation.
%C A397707 Each translation class of a single cell contains 4 orientations of the cell, so a(1) = 4. A385028 counts the same polyforms up to rotation and reflection of the honeycomb as well; a(n)/A385028(n) tends to 16, the order of the point group of the honeycomb (verified for n <= 11).
%H A397707 Bert Dobbelaere, Peter Kagey, Drake Thomas, and Andrés R. Vindas-Meléndez, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.23301">Building with Blocks: Enumerating Polyforms on Tilings</a>, arXiv:2602.23301 [math.CO], 2026.
%H A397707 Tyler Satchel Orden, <a href="https://github.com/Tyorden/bisymmetric-hendecahedron-polyforms">Code, tables, and run logs</a>.
%e A397707 A single cell occurs in 4 orientations that are not related by a translation of the honeycomb, so a(1) = 4.
%Y A397707 Cf. A385028 (counted up to rotation and reflection as well), A001931 (analog for the cubic honeycomb).
%K A397707 nonn,more,new
%O A397707 1,1
%A A397707 _Tyler Satchel Orden_, Jul 05 2026
